<h1>Network-Simulator</h1>
<ul>
<li>A simple network simulator to create network topologies, featuring devices like PCs, routers, and switches.</li>
<li>Each device features a command line/interface for configuring IP addresses, VLANs, access/trunk ports, default gateways, and more.</li>
<li>Current working functionality includes ICMP pings, ARP learning process, and dynamic MAC address learning.</li>
<li>Defined PDUs for OSI layers 2, 3 and 4, including encapsulation and de-encapsulation at each layer.
<br></li>
<li>As of 9/4/2023 trunk ports are still under development.</li>
</ul>
<p>(They can be configured, but they do not operate as expected)</p>